1
00:01:45,916 --> 00:01:47,000
[gasps]

2
00:01:47,083 --> 00:01:50,083
They’re shutting it down
for good?

3
00:01:50,166 --> 00:01:52,625
[wailing cry]

4
00:01:52,708 --> 00:01:55,333
Meow!

5
00:02:00,541 --> 00:02:02,500
[shimmering]

6
00:02:02,583 --> 00:02:05,416
[bell chimes]

7
00:02:07,583 --> 00:02:09,250
♪

8
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:11,083
It’s almost over.

9
00:02:12,125 --> 00:02:13,666
[grunting]

10
00:02:18,166 --> 00:02:19,833
[grunting continues]

11
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:23,291
Meow!

12
00:02:25,458 --> 00:02:28,041
The world is ending for good.

13
00:02:31,625 --> 00:02:34,958
And so are my adventures
with you, Rei.

14
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:40,791
[REI]
Father. What is this?

15
00:02:40,875 --> 00:02:44,083
[YUUKI] I want you to hold onto
it for a while.

16
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:45,625
If something were to happen,

17
00:02:45,708 --> 00:02:49,333
follow the instructions
inside it to the letter.

18
00:02:49,416 --> 00:02:51,958
Nothing specific,
just... “something"?

19
00:02:52,041 --> 00:02:54,250
Can you give me
a little more than that?

20
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:56,750
Nothing to worry about, dear.

21
00:02:56,833 --> 00:02:59,416
Merely a precaution.

22
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,500
Dungeon Century was nothing
but a prototype.

23
00:03:01,583 --> 00:03:03,500
It has served its purpose.

24
00:03:05,375 --> 00:03:08,291
It’s time for my new creation
to take its place.

25
00:03:08,375 --> 00:03:11,083
This will be the game
that truly changes the world.

26
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:15,458
A reality beyond reality.
A masterpiece.

27
00:03:15,541 --> 00:03:17,000
Beyond reality?

28
00:03:19,416 --> 00:03:20,708
Yes.

29
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:22,666
I realize it’s poor timing,
on my part,

30
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,708
now that you’ve found
a partner you like.

31
00:03:24,791 --> 00:03:25,875
[gasps]

32
00:03:25,958 --> 00:03:28,333
What?
Have you been spying on me?

33
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:30,458
Sorry.
You’re my precious daughter.

34
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:32,833
I was worried about you,
that’s all.

35
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:36,000
[REI]
Daddy, you’re the worst!

36
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:37,625
[YUUKI]
Yes, I know.

37
00:03:37,708 --> 00:03:39,166
[chuckling]

38
00:03:40,583 --> 00:03:42,583
Gwin!
[laughs]

39
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:49,125
Meow!

40
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:50,500
Meow.

41
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:57,041
-What’s his problem?
-Hush! He’ll hear you. Let's go.

42
00:04:00,208 --> 00:04:02,500
I told him
he’d crash and burn.

43
00:04:02,583 --> 00:04:04,125
Ranshou! Wait up!

44
00:04:04,208 --> 00:04:05,625
[RANSHOU]
What’s wrong, Suigin?

45
00:04:05,708 --> 00:04:07,166
I was under the impression

46
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:09,625
that you enjoyed
your nightly rendezvous.

47
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:13,375
[SUIGIN] Yeah, till the world
decided to end.

48
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:15,583
What’s that supposed to mean?

49
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:17,750
[chuckles] Come on, man.

50
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:20,833
Just because the game is ending
doesn’t mean it’s over.

51
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:24,833
All you need to do is get closer
to her outside of it.

52
00:04:24,916 --> 00:04:26,291
[SUIGIN]
I can't.

53
00:04:26,375 --> 00:04:29,958
She only knows the "me"
in-game, not the real me.

54
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:31,458
Hold on a second.

55
00:04:31,541 --> 00:04:34,083
You love her, but you’ve
never actually met before?

56
00:04:35,083 --> 00:04:36,750
[SUIGIN]
Can’t be helped.

57
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:39,583
We live in two completely
different worlds.

58
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:42,250
Meow!

59
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:46,416
[FEMALE STUDENT]
I hope he’ll be okay.

60
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:49,250
[RANSHOU] Don’t worry.
Even if the flames consume him,

61
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,666
I know he’ll rise again
from the ashes.

62
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:54,541
That’s just the kind of guy
Suigin is.

63
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:56,791
You’re such
a great friend to him.

64
00:04:56,875 --> 00:04:57,833
[chuckles]

65
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:00,708
[SUIGIN]
Work.

66
00:05:00,791 --> 00:05:03,500
-[shimmering]
-[laughter]

67
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:07,875
I need to get to work.

68
00:05:07,958 --> 00:05:10,250
[car approaches]

69
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:14,500
[DRIVER]
I have your schedule, sir.

70
00:05:14,583 --> 00:05:15,916
We need to be at the office

71
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,375
at 4 PM for
an executive meeting.

72
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:20,833
After that, President Ling needs
to go over the particulars

73
00:05:20,916 --> 00:05:23,166
of the new game’s
announcement with you.

74
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:25,250
[YUUKI]
Hmm.

75
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:26,666
[typing]

76
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:28,333
[MAKI]
Rei, go to bed!

77
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:31,500
Staying up late every night
is murder for your complexion.

78
00:05:31,583 --> 00:05:34,791
I’ll be okay.
Don’t worry.

79
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:38,500
[sighs, laughs] Well, don’t say
I didn’t warn you.

80
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:40,125
Sweet dreams, Maki.

81
00:05:41,875 --> 00:05:44,500
[typing]

82
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:47,041
[bell chimes]

83
00:05:47,125 --> 00:05:48,583
♪

84
00:05:48,666 --> 00:05:50,333
[PLAYER 1]
This is bogus!

85
00:05:50,416 --> 00:05:52,500
Why didn’t they make a public
statement about the shut-down?

86
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:54,000
This was so out of the blue!

87
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:55,750
[PLAYER 2] Especially after
all the time and money

88
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:56,958
I spent on this game.

89
00:05:57,041 --> 00:05:59,166
[PLAYER 3]
Seriously!

90
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:01,416
[PLAYER 1] On another note,
did you hear the rumor?

91
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,500
Apparently they added
a new rare item.

92
00:06:03,583 --> 00:06:05,583
There’s only one copy,
and if you find it,

93
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,166
it’ll grant you a wish.

94
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:09,208
You’re talking about
the Evening Song Flower, right?

95
00:06:09,291 --> 00:06:10,625
[PLAYER 2]
If we found it,

96
00:06:10,708 --> 00:06:12,375
we could wish
for the game to continue!

97
00:06:12,458 --> 00:06:15,291
[PLAYER 1] Sure, that’ll happen.
Don’t be stupid.

98
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:16,916
[GAME PLAYERS chuckle]

99
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,291
[PLAYER 1] Still, I can’t
believe it’ll be over soon.

100
00:06:20,375 --> 00:06:22,666
[PLAYER 2] Guess we’ll have to
go all-out until that happens.

101
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:32,625
[REI] Where are you?
C'mon, Gwin.

102
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:37,208
-[grunting]
-Meow!

103
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:43,666
[sighs]

104
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:46,000
[typing]

105
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:49,291
♪

106
00:06:49,375 --> 00:06:52,541
This is one of the last times
I’ll get to play with you.

107
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:00,791
I hate it.

108
00:07:00,875 --> 00:07:03,291
But there’s nothing
I can do to change it.

109
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:06,916
Meow!

110
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:14,250
Well, there you are, Gwin!
I’ve been waiting!

111
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,833
You must have been busy.

112
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:24,500
It’s okay. You’re here now.

113
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:30,500
We only have a week
before all of this ends for us.

114
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:37,000
So, until it does...

115
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:42,250
I say we enjoy every adventure
this game has to offer.

116
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:44,833
Let’s get going!
[laughs]

117
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:49,416
[SUIGIN] I see.
As far as she’s concerned...

118
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:52,708
this is just one game
among countless others.

119
00:07:52,791 --> 00:07:54,208
And me?

120
00:07:54,291 --> 00:07:57,000
I’m just one of her
many gaming buddies.

121
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:01,083
[SUIGIN]
But, is that really so bad?

122
00:08:03,958 --> 00:08:10,291
Even now, in this game,
it’s just you and me.

123
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:15,166
In this place.
I’m able to be with you.

124
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:21,125
[rain pouring]

125
00:08:33,625 --> 00:08:35,500
[REI]
Hey, Gwin.

126
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:38,000
Did you hear?

127
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:41,583
They just added a rare variant
of the Song Flower in-game.

128
00:08:41,666 --> 00:08:45,083
No matter what happens,
I want to find it.

129
00:08:52,458 --> 00:08:55,041
They call it
the Evening Song Flower.

130
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:56,291
Here.

131
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,875
Apparently it grows in one field
out of the whole game world.

132
00:09:03,958 --> 00:09:06,583
I know we only have
a week left to play.

133
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:09,166
But I’d really like to find it,
if we could.

134
00:09:13,458 --> 00:09:15,333
Uh.
Yes?

135
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:24,666
Are you saying you want to try?

136
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,250
You'll find it with me?

137
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:35,208
Oh! Oh, Gwin, you’re the best!
Thank you so much!

138
00:09:36,916 --> 00:09:38,166
[whooping, laughing]

139
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,416
[water splashing]

140
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:42,208
[REI laughing]

141
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:46,083
[SUIGIN]
Together. With you.

142
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:53,875
[typing]

143
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:56,458
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
Good evening, world!

144
00:09:56,541 --> 00:09:58,166
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER]
Good evening, world!

145
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:00,000
[MALE ANNOUNCER] We at
the God Grave Tech Company

146
00:10:00,083 --> 00:10:03,166
proudly present
our latest creation!

147
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:04,541
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER]
The ultimate

148
00:10:04,625 --> 00:10:07,708
in massive-multiplayer
online entertainment!

149
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:11,666
[BOTH]
We call it, Grave Buster!

150
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:13,291
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
In Grave Buster,

151
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:16,208
each player will take
on the role of a grave robber.

152
00:10:16,291 --> 00:10:20,250
Their goal: to loot the various
treasures within each stage.

153
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:21,875
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER] And to help
you with this endeavor,

154
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:23,708
we’re introducing
a new system.

155
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:27,833
Your ultimate strength
will be your financial strength!

156
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:30,083
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
The more players pay,

157
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:31,750
the more powerful
their characters

158
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:33,541
will eventually become!

159
00:10:33,625 --> 00:10:35,541
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER]
Additionally, all players

160
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:36,750
who sign up will receive

161
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:39,000
a specially designed console
for free!

162
00:10:39,083 --> 00:10:42,541
Seabay, the platform
of Grave Buster!

163
00:10:42,625 --> 00:10:44,041
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
Now, get out there

164
00:10:44,125 --> 00:10:45,833
and raid some tombs!

165
00:10:45,916 --> 00:10:47,958
[BOTH] And aim for supreme
financial power!

166
00:10:48,041 --> 00:10:49,916
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
There are countless treasures

167
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,250
just waiting for you!

168
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:53,416
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER]
Only you can dig them up!

169
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:55,875
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
A reality beyond reality!

170
00:10:55,958 --> 00:11:00,208
[BOTH] That is the essence
of Grave Buster!

171
00:11:00,291 --> 00:11:02,500
Looks like the announcement
went off without a hitch,

172
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:04,125
just as we expected.

173
00:11:04,208 --> 00:11:07,291
We couldn’t have done it
without your genius.

174
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:11,083
The name Yuuki Riku will forever
be synonymous with game design.

175
00:11:11,166 --> 00:11:12,333
Hmph.

176
00:11:12,416 --> 00:11:14,416
This is only the beginning,
my friend.

177
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:19,333
Soon you’ll see my “vision.”

178
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:22,083
[MALE ANNOUNCER]
Reality beyond reality!

179
00:11:22,166 --> 00:11:24,250
[BOTH]
Grave Buster!

180
00:11:27,208 --> 00:11:30,000
[birds chirping]

181
00:11:30,083 --> 00:11:31,333
[grunts]

182
00:11:32,708 --> 00:11:35,125
[REI]
Gwin! Over here!

183
00:11:36,791 --> 00:11:38,166
[chuckling]

184
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:17,375
[SUIGIN]
The Silver Guardian.

